Added a `select_related` on every per-type FK column to the `CableViewSet` and `CableToCableTerminationViewSet` querysets and switched `Cable._get_termination_attr` to iterate the prefetched `terminations` cache so listing cables no longer runs an N+1 of queries per join row.
Added a `Meta.default_m2m_fields` extension to `nautobot.core.api.serializers.OptInFieldsMixin`. Subclasses can list ListSerializer / ManyRelatedField source names that should be included in API responses by default (alongside the global `DEFAULT_M2M_FIELDS` of `tags`/`content_types`/`object_types`) without requiring callers to pass `?exclude_m2m=False`.
Added writability to the `terminations` field on the `Cable` REST API serializer. POST and PATCH on `/api/dcim/cables/` now accept a `terminations` list whose entries are matched on `(cable_end, connector)`: providing a per-type FK (e.g. `interface: <uuid>`) creates or replaces the join row, omitting all per-type FKs (or setting them to null) deletes the row, and rows not present in the payload are left untouched (sparse PATCH semantics). The entire payload is applied in a single transaction; per-row validation is delegated to `CableToCableTerminationSerializer` so model-level errors come back as 400.
